message.content:
A 'Calidris melanotos' is a shorebird belonging to the Sandpiper family.
It has a small body size ranging from 15-20 cm in length and weighing around 25-50 grams.
The bird has a distinctive black and white feather pattern on its wings and back.
The head, neck, and breast are light brown in color with some individuals having a reddish tint.
They have a straight, slender beak that is dark brown or black in color.
Their legs are relatively long and thin, with a black hue that stands out against their light-colored feathers.
Calidris melanotos can be found in sand and muddy beaches, shallow freshwater marshes, and wet grasslands across Eurasia and North America.
